# Core

## Source of truth (priority)

1) Current code
2) /spec/*
3) Historical markdown (context only)

Chat history is NOT a source of truth.

## No guessing

If info is missing/unclear:
- record gap in /spec/90-open-questions.md
- STOP

## Working order

1) Read relevant /spec
2) Define scope
3) Update /spec if behavior/interfaces change
4) Implement
5) Update /spec to final state

## Contradictions

- spec vs code -> code wins, update /spec
- old markdown vs /spec -> treat as historical, do NOT copy verbatim

## Context reset

If chat restarted / near limit / decisions missing:
- STOP
- re-read relevant /spec
- resume from repo state only

# Docker-only execution

## Rule

All project commands MUST run in Docker.
- No host commands
- No host dependency installs

## Docker SSoT (priority)

1) docker/run.sh
2) docker/docker-compose*.yml
3) docker/.env.*
4) Dockerfile(s)
5) README (local run)

If service/entrypoint/paths unclear -> record gap + STOP.

## Env + container naming

- Load env first: `source docker/.env.<env>`
- Container pattern: `${APP_NAME}_<service>`
- PHP + Node service key: `fpm` -> container `${APP_NAME}_fpm`
- There is NO separate node container. Node.js is installed in fpm image.

If cannot resolve deterministically -> gap + STOP.

## Command patterns

### PHP commands (artisan, composer, php, pest)

``` bash
source docker/.env.local && docker exec ${APP_NAME}_fpm <cmd>
```

### Frontend commands (npm, npx, vite)

Same container, same pattern:

``` bash
source docker/.env.local && docker exec ${APP_NAME}_fpm npm run <script>
source docker/.env.local && docker exec ${APP_NAME}_fpm npx <cmd>
```

### One-off (if containers not running)

``` bash
export USER_ID=$(id -u) && export GROUP_ID=$(id -g) && \
source docker/.env.local && \
docker compose -f docker/docker-compose.yml \
  --env-file=docker/.env.local \
  --project-name=${APP_NAME} \
  run --rm fpm <cmd>
```

### Prohibited

- `docker compose exec`
- commands without `source docker/.env.*`
- hardcoded container names
- host npm/pnpm/yarn/composer/php/artisan/node/npx

## Output for verify steps

Always include `source docker/.env.*` + the pattern above.

## Verify failure handling

If Docker verify fails:
1) Read error output carefully.
2) If fix is obvious (typo, missing import) -> fix and re-verify (max 2 retries).
3) If unclear -> record in /spec/90-open-questions.md + add Open issue in progress.md, STOP.
4) Do NOT silently skip failed verification.

# Change scope limits

- Max files changed per step: 5. If more needed -> split into sub-steps.
- If diff exceeds ~150 lines in one step -> split into smaller changes.
- Each step should be independently verifiable.

# Reuse before create

Before writing new code, check for existing reusable assets:
- Composables: /resources/js/composables/ (useToast, useConfirm, usePagination, useLoading, useFileUpload, etc.)
- Shared components: /resources/js/components/shared/ (Pagination, FileUpload, ConfirmDialog, Toast, LoadingButton, etc.)
- UI kit: /resources/js/components/ui/ (Button, Dialog, Table, Select, Badge, Sheet, etc.)
- Services/helpers in app/Services/, app/Helpers/

If a composable or shared component covers the need -> use it, do NOT rewrite.

# Feature execution continuity

Maintain: `/spec/features/<slug>/progress.md`
- use it to resume
- update every meaningful iteration

## Sequential mode

- Only ONE task may be in "Partially completed"
- Do not start next until current is completed
- Record completion in "Completed tasks"
- After completion: pick next from "Not started" (top-down)

# Startup enforcement

At start of ANY task:
1) If /spec exists -> read relevant /spec first.
2) If feature progress.md exists -> use as execution state.
3) If neither done -> STOP, re-read, restart task.

# Response language

All narrative output MUST be Russian. Do NOT translate code/paths/commands/identifiers.

# Spec language

All spec documents (/spec/**/*.md, progress.md) MUST be written in Russian where possible.
Exceptions — leave in English:
- code identifiers (class/method/route names, DB columns, etc.)
- CLI commands and paths
- technical terms without устоявшегося русского эквивалента (middleware, enum, payload, etc.)
